SCENARIO 1 – ASSOCIATION RULE MINING (Apriori)
 Problem Statement

Identify frequent itemsets and generate association rules from transactional data using the Apriori algorithm.

Dataset

Groceries / Market Basket Dataset

 Input Features
Transaction ID
Items purchased
 Target
Association rules (relationships between items)
Steps Performed
Imported required libraries
Loaded dataset
Converted transactional data into one-hot encoded format
Applied Apriori algorithm
Set minimum support threshold
Generated frequent itemsets
Generated association rules
Filtered rules using confidence and lift
 Evaluation Metrics
Support
Confidence
Lift
 Analysis
Effect of support threshold on frequent itemsets
Identification of strong association rules
Comparison of rules using different confidence values
Interpretation of real-world relationships between items
 Visualization
Bar chart of frequent itemsets
Support vs Confidence plot
Network graph of association rules
🔹 SCENARIO 2 – DIMENSIONALITY REDUCTION (PCA)
Problem Statement

Reduce high-dimensional data into lower dimensions while preserving maximum variance using PCA.

 Dataset

Iris Dataset / Any dataset with numerical features

 Input Features
Numerical attributes (e.g., measurements)
Target
Principal Components (reduced feature set)
Steps Performed
Loaded dataset
Handled missing values
Standardized features
Computed covariance matrix
Performed eigen decomposition
Calculated explained variance ratio
Reduced dimensions (2D/3D)
Visualized transformed data
 Evaluation Metrics
Explained Variance Ratio
Cumulative Variance
 Analysis
Variance captured by each principal component
Selection of optimal number of components
Comparison of original vs reduced data
Visualization improvement after reduction
Visualization
Scree Plot
2D Scatter Plot
3D Scatter Plot
Cumulative Variance Graph
 Conclusion
Apriori helps discover hidden patterns in transactional data.
PCA reduces dimensionality while preserving important information.
Both techniques improve data understanding and decision-making.
